What kind of insurance is right for me?
Car insurance that protects the driver in the event of an accident is a considerable expense that depends on various factors such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of a driving licence, type of vehicle to be insured or used, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing a suitable car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to figure out what we're talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured person.
This obligation takes the form of an insurance contract which provides that the insurance undertaking will receive an agreed insurance amount of a certain amount for taking care of the payment of damages in the event of an insurance event.
Insurance is the price of insurance which is determined in respect of various factors such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of a driving licence, type of vehicle which is insured or used, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so the greater the likelihood of an accident, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both 25-year-olds and women must pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, on the basis of the checks, insurance companies concluded that persons living in a marriage have fewer accidents than free drivers.
The way in which the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of driving and thus the probability of having an accident.
The growth in driving rates increases the probability.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when setting the premium price.
Therefore, the driver has to study the situation well in order to choose the insurance that is best suited to his profile of the insured person.
We will show here the most important variables for the selection of one or the other type of insurance, which, in addition to satisfying the type of insured person, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under 25 years of age encounter different disadvantages such as little experience in driving and short possession of a driving licence when they want to arrange insurance at an affordable price.
Although ideal for good coverage is insurance against all risks, there are also cheaper variants.
The most careful drivers may choose insurance against all risks with a discount of insurance to obtain insurance coverage of all risks but at the most acceptable price.
This kind of contract would assume the client's involvement in the payment of the insurance event.
"Part of the payment of the insurance event provided by the client will be determined in advance when determining the premium price, which will be the higher, how lower would be the participation', explains Luis Noguera, head of First Europe in Spain, Internet insurance intermediary.
Another option is insurance extended to other participants in the operation so that the client will be insured against damage caused to other persons, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, he would be insured against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
Recommendations.
If you are under 25 years of age, try to be attentive and avoid accidents as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce insurance premiums in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate held by the insurance company.
On the other hand, malus is the increase in the basic rate mentioned.
"Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company had a good year, it will be able to afford to raise the bonus" explains Noguera.
After crossing the border of twenty-five years, it is easier for drivers to arrange insurance because the client risk index decreases, thanks to acquired experience.
For this reason, it is most recommended to arrange insurance against all risks at a discount.
"Young people are usually unable to take advantage of the experience acquired in advance at the moment of the accident and even during driving', the director of the European company in Spain assures and adds that most of the accidents occur in the second year of the procedure when the "fear of the newcomer" has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better to arrange insurance against all risks, provided that his economic situation permits it.
Families with children are considered as clients with the lowest risk index and therefore their increases will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with a premium discount (which could be EUR 300) or with a high bonus, insurance extended to other participants in the operation, starting from the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
"Their driving is calmer and their purchasing capacity is higher, so they can afford luxury to get the highest discount," notes Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are recommended to cover all risks with a premium discount (EUR 150) or insurance extended to other participants in the operation if a high bonus has been achieved.
It should be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects drivers in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a considerable expense, which is a valid reason to properly study the possibilities of insurance that would suit us most in the face of our personal situation.
