Previous events are a tangled, confusing chain of artistic and curatorial events.
Warhol made his first Brillo boxes in New York in 1964, painting wooden boxes that were based on the red and brittle design of Brillo soap cartons.
The exhibition of his works in Moderna Museet in 1968 showed - with Warhol's consent - hundreds of Brillo boxes made of cardboard. These were not (for financial reasons) from Warhol but were delivered directly from the Brillo factory.
