The Witnesses at that time now speak of fifteen boxes that were rightfully entered into art and auction history as authorized originals - "Andy Warholovy Brillo Boxy" with the designation Type Stockholm.
Some of them were sold out at auctions for over $100,000.
The problem now lies in the fact that the legendary director of the Pontus Hultén Museum later falsely claimed that in 1968 it was produced and exhibited in Sweden about a hundred cases, which Warhol then left to him.
In fact, 105 of Hultén's cases were only produced in Malmö for the exhibition in St Petersburg in 1990.
By that time, Warhol was already three years dead.
